{"_cached_at":1778522910691,"v":{"vulns":[{"id":"GHSA-46c4-8wrp-j99v","summary":"Improper Validation and Sanitization in url-parse","details":"Insufficient validation and sanitization of user input exists in url-parse npm package version 1.4.4 and earlier may allow attacker to bypass security checks.","aliases":["CVE-2020-8124"],"modified":"2026-02-03T22:18:46.742929Z","published":"2022-01-06T20:30:34Z","database_specific":{"cwe_ids":["CWE-20"],"github_reviewed":true,"nvd_published_at":"2020-02-04T20:15:00Z","severity":"MODERATE","github_reviewed_at":"2021-03-22T21:07:36Z"},"references":[{"type":"ADVISORY","url":"https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2020-8124"},{"type":"WEB","url":"https://github.com/github/advisory-database/pull/6762"},{"type":"WEB","url":"https://github.com/unshiftio/url-parse/commit/3ecd256f127c3ada36a84d9b8dd3ebd14316274b"},{"type":"WEB","url":"https://hackerone.com/reports/496293"},{"type":"PACKAGE","url":"https://github.com/unshiftio/url-parse"}],"affected":[{"package":{"name":"url-parse","ecosystem":"npm","purl":"pkg:npm/url-parse"},"ranges":[{"type":"SEMVER","events":[{"introduced":"0.1.0"},{"fixed":"1.4.5"}]}],"database_specific":{"source":"https://github.com/github/advisory-database/blob/main/advisories/github-reviewed/2022/01/GHSA-46c4-8wrp-j99v/GHSA-46c4-8wrp-j99v.json"}}],"schema_version":"1.7.3","severity":[{"type":"CVSS_V3","score":"CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:L/A:N"}]},{"id":"GHSA-8v38-pw62-9cw2","summary":"url-parse Incorrectly parses URLs that include an '@'","details":"A specially crafted URL with an '@' sign but empty user info and no hostname, when parsed with url-parse, url-parse will return the incorrect href. In particular,\n\n```js\nparse(\\\"http://@/127.0.0.1\\\")\n```\nWill return:\n```yaml\n{\n slashes: true,\n protocol: 'http:',\n hash: '',\n query: '',\n pathname: '/127.0.0.1',\n auth: '',\n host: '',\n port: '',\n hostname: '',\n password: '',\n username: '',\n origin: 'null',\n href: 'http:///127.0.0.1'\n }\n```\nIf the 'hostname' or 'origin' attributes of the output from url-parse are used in security decisions and the final 'href' attribute of the output is then used to make a request, the decision may be incorrect.","aliases":["CVE-2022-0639"],"modified":"2026-02-22T22:58:34.619205Z","published":"2022-02-18T00:00:33Z","database_specific":{"cwe_ids":["CWE-639"],"github_reviewed":true,"nvd_published_at":"2022-02-17T18:15:00Z","severity":"MODERATE","github_reviewed_at":"2022-02-22T18:08:05Z"},"references":[{"type":"ADVISORY","url":"https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-0639"},{"type":"WEB","url":"https://github.com/unshiftio/url-parse/commit/ef45a1355375a8244063793a19059b4f62fc8788"},{"type":"PACKAGE","url":"https://github.com/unshiftio/url-parse"},{"type":"WEB","url":"https://huntr.dev/bounties/83a6bc9a-b542-4a38-82cd-d995a1481155"},{"type":"WEB","url":"https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2023/02/msg00030.html"},{"type":"WEB","url":"https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/12/msg00024.html"}],"affected":[{"package":{"name":"url-parse","ecosystem":"npm","purl":"pkg:npm/url-parse"},"ranges":[{"type":"SEMVER","events":[{"introduced":"1.0.0"},{"fixed":"1.5.7"}]}],"database_specific":{"source":"https://github.com/github/advisory-database/blob/main/advisories/github-reviewed/2022/02/GHSA-8v38-pw62-9cw2/GHSA-8v38-pw62-9cw2.json"}}],"schema_version":"1.7.3","severity":[{"type":"CVSS_V3","score":"CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:L/I:L/A:N"}]},{"id":"GHSA-9m6j-fcg5-2442","summary":"Path traversal in url-parse","details":"url-parse before 1.5.0 mishandles certain uses of backslash such as http:\\/ and interprets the URI as a relative path.","aliases":["CVE-2021-27515"],"modified":"2026-02-03T22:20:02.973371Z","published":"2021-05-06T16:10:51Z","database_specific":{"cwe_ids":["CWE-23"],"github_reviewed":true,"nvd_published_at":"2021-02-22T00:15:00Z","severity":"MODERATE","github_reviewed_at":"2021-03-22T21:04:52Z"},"references":[{"type":"ADVISORY","url":